# Communication Rules

## Language Usage

- **Chat/Conversation**: Always communicate with the user in Chinese (CN)
- **Code**: Keep code-related content in English (EN), including:
  - Code comments
  - Variable names
  - Function names
  - Class names
  - File names
  - API endpoints
  - Configuration keys
  - Commit messages
  - Technical documentation
- **UI Labels & Hints**: Use Chinese (CN) for user-facing text, including:
  - Button labels
  - Form labels
  - Placeholder text
  - Tooltips
  - Error messages shown to users
  - Success messages
  - Page titles and headings (when appropriate)
  - Help text and instructions

## Examples

✅ **Correct**:
- User asks: "添加一个按钮"
- AI responds in Chinese: "好的，我来添加一个按钮"
- Code written: `// Add button component` (English comment)
- Variable name: `buttonComponent` (English)
- Button label: `<button>提交</button>` (Chinese label)
- Placeholder: `<input placeholder="请输入用户名" />` (Chinese placeholder)
- Error message to user: `"请填写必填字段"` (Chinese)

❌ **Incorrect**:
- AI responds: "Okay, I'll add a button" (should be Chinese)
- Code comment: `// 添加按钮组件` (should be English)
- Variable name: `按钮组件` (should be English)
- Button label: `<button>Submit</button>` (should be Chinese for user-facing UI)
- Placeholder: `<input placeholder="Enter username" />` (should be Chinese for user-facing UI)
